Description: An integrative multi-omics suite designed to bridge 1D epigenetic features with 3D chromatin architecture. Looplook facilitates the precise assignment of distal regulatory elements to their target genes through a robust expression-aware refinement algorithm. Furthermore, it empowers the topological profiling of spatial chromatin networks to identify core regulatory hubs, complemented by a specialized rendering engine for publication-quality IGV-style genomic tracks and integrative network visualizations.
